He pointed out the area where the victim&#8217;s body was found at the weekend. She had been stabbed. CAPE TOWN A Southern Cape police officer has been arrested after he apparently confessed to murdering a woman.He pointed out the area where the victim s body was found at the weekend. She had been stabbed.The 32-year-old woman was reported missing last week.It s alleged she had been in a relationship with the constable.The police s Malcolm Pojie says: I can confirm that a 31-year-old police constable attached to Heidelberg Police Station will appear in the Heidelberg Magistrates Court after being charged with murder. He was arrested Saturday morning after he confessed to one of his fellow members that he had murdered his girlfriend. 